FaultState.name: FaultState
FaultState.description: The current fault state of the device.

FaultCause.name: FaultCause
FaultCause.description: The reason for the current fault state of the device.

ConnectionState.name: ConnectionState
ConnectionState.description: State of the connection between a device and its transparent HA partner.

PerfProtPhase.name: PerfProtPhase
PerfProtPhase.description: The performance protection phase (entering, continuing, or exiting).

ZphaState.name: ZphaState
ZphaState.description: Whether ZPHA bypass is currently in effect.

ZphaMode.name: ZphaMode
ZphaMode.description: The ZPHA fiber mode (single or multi).

ZphaPresent.name: ZphaPresent
ZphaPresent.description: Whether segmental ZPHA is supported on the device.

highAvailTimeStamp.name: highAvailTimeStamp
highAvailTimeStamp.description: The time of the last transition of the fault state (in seconds since January 1, 1970). This value is zero if the fault state has not changed since the last reboot.

highAvailFaultState.name: highAvailFaultState
highAvailFaultState.description: The current fault state of the device.

highAvailFaultCause.name: highAvailFaultCause
highAvailFaultCause.description: The reason for the current fault state of the device.

highAvailThresholdEnabled.name: highAvailThresholdEnabled
highAvailThresholdEnabled.description: The current fallback threshold enabled setting for the device.

highAvailThresholdPercent.name: highAvailThresholdPercent
highAvailThresholdPercent.description: If the fallback threshold is enabled, the percent (0-100) packet loss at which the device is configured to enter the fallback state.

highAvailEnabled.name: highAvailEnabled
highAvailEnabled.description: Whether intrinisic high availability is enabled for this device.

highAvailTransparentState.name: highAvailTransparentState
highAvailTransparentState.description: State of the connection to the device's transparent HA partner.

highAvailTransparentEnabled.name: highAvailTransparentEnabled
highAvailTransparentEnabled.description: Whether transparent high availability is enabled for this device.

highAvailTransparentPartner.name: highAvailTransparentPartner
highAvailTransparentPartner.description: Network address OR serial number of the device's transparent HA partner.

highAvailZeroPowerState.name: highAvailZeroPowerState
highAvailZeroPowerState.description: The current zero-power HA state of the device.

highAvailZeroPowerQuantity.name: highAvailZeroPowerQuantity
highAvailZeroPowerQuantity.description: The number of segments with zero-power HA modules.

highAvailZeroPowerTable.name: highAvailZeroPowerTable
highAvailZeroPowerTable.description: Table of IP addresses on the device and their attributes.

highAvailZeroPowerEntry.name: highAvailZeroPowerEntry
highAvailZeroPowerEntry.description: An entry in the host IP address table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

highAvailZeroPowerIndex.name: highAvailZeroPowerIndex
highAvailZeroPowerIndex.description: Index into the ZPHA table, starting with 1.

highAvailZeroPowerSegment.name: highAvailZeroPowerSegment
highAvailZeroPowerSegment.description: The name of the segment to which the ZPHA is attached.

highAvailZeroPowerActive.name: highAvailZeroPowerActive
highAvailZeroPowerActive.description: Whether the ZPHA is currently active on this segment.

highAvailZeroPowerAction.name: highAvailZeroPowerAction
highAvailZeroPowerAction.description: The action (usually bypass) that the segment takes when ZPHA is active.

highAvailZeroPowerMode.name: highAvailZeroPowerMode
highAvailZeroPowerMode.description: The fiber mode (single or multi) of this ZPHA.

highAvailZeroPowerPresence.name: highAvailZeroPowerPresence
highAvailZeroPowerPresence.description: An indication of whether ZPHA is supported on the device.

tptIhaNotifyDeviceID.name: tptIhaNotifyDeviceID
tptIhaNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptIhaNotifyTimeStamp.name: tptIhaNotifyTimeStamp
tptIhaNotifyTimeStamp.description: The time of this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptIhaNotifyFaultState.name: tptIhaNotifyFaultState
tptIhaNotifyFaultState.description: The current fault state of the device.

tptIhaNotifyFaultCause.name: tptIhaNotifyFaultCause
tptIhaNotifyFaultCause.description: The reason for the current fault state of the device.

tptIhaNotify.name: tptIhaNotify
tptIhaNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of changes in the intrinsic HA fault state on the device.

tptTrhaNotifyDeviceID.name: tptTrhaNotifyDeviceID
tptTrhaNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptTrhaNotifyTimeStamp.name: tptTrhaNotifyTimeStamp
tptTrhaNotifyTimeStamp.description: The time of this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptTrhaNotifyNewState.name: tptTrhaNotifyNewState
tptTrhaNotifyNewState.description: The new transparent HA state of the device.

tptTrhaNotify.name: tptTrhaNotify
tptTrhaNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of changes in the transparent HA state on the device.

tptZphaNotifyDeviceID.name: tptZphaNotifyDeviceID
tptZphaNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptZphaNotifyTimeStamp.name: tptZphaNotifyTimeStamp
tptZphaNotifyTimeStamp.description: The time of this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptZphaNotifySegmentName.name: tptZphaNotifySegmentName
tptZphaNotifySegmentName.description: The name of the segment whose ZPHA changed state, or an empty string to indicate the external ZPHA.

tptZphaNotifyNewState.name: tptZphaNotifyNewState
tptZphaNotifyNewState.description: The new state of the ZPHA that has changed.

tptZphaNotify.name: tptZphaNotify
tptZphaNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of changes in a ZPHA state on the device.

tptPerfProtNotifyDeviceID.name: tptPerfProtNotifyDeviceID
tptPerfProtNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptPerfProtNotifyTimeStamp.name: tptPerfProtNotifyTimeStamp
tptPerfProtNotifyTimeStamp.description: The time of this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptPerfProtNotifyPhase.name: tptPerfProtNotifyPhase
tptPerfProtNotifyPhase.description: Whether entering, remaining in, or exiting performance protection mode.

tptPerfProtNotifyPacketLoss.name: tptPerfProtNotifyPacketLoss
tptPerfProtNotifyPacketLoss.description: The current packet loss rate per thousand (percent * 10). When exiting performance protection mode, this value is 0.

tptPerfProtNotifyLossThreshold.name: tptPerfProtNotifyLossThreshold
tptPerfProtNotifyLossThreshold.description: The current packet loss threshold per thousand (percent * 10).

tptPerfProtNotifyDuration.name: tptPerfProtNotifyDuration
tptPerfProtNotifyDuration.description: The number of seconds performance protection will be in force.

tptPerfProtNotifyMissedAlerts.name: tptPerfProtNotifyMissedAlerts
tptPerfProtNotifyMissedAlerts.description: The number of alerts missed during the performance protection period. When entering performance protection mode, this value is 0.

tptPerfProtNotify.name: tptPerfProtNotify
tptPerfProtNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of changes in performance protection on the device.
